node.text: JC and Henok make time to catch up on their friendship that formed during the first Rate Beer fest and how Omnipollo's intriguing intersection of beer, pop culture and artistic exploration resonates so much with JC. Fast forward today and hear about how @omnipollo beer is available all over the world while at the same time setting down deeper roots in Sweden. We hit refresh on Covered In Puppies, our collaboration DIPA and its drinking beautifully. We miss you Henok & Karl!

node.text:
We've recently had the opportunity to work on a unique collaboration with the team at @brocktonbeer for this year's upcoming @barrelandflow festival in Pittsburgh, which we were honored to be asked to participate in.

Given our shared vision and efforts for community and sense of place, working with Pierre, Eval, and Rowan was a no-brainer!

We knew we wanted to offer something that could achieve the kind of excitement and enjoyment that we always strive for, but take a deeply intentional approach that represents the contextual purpose of Barrel & Flow and the resulting conversations that this opportunity deserves.

Cultures have a near-universal connection to baking and the communal "breaking" of bread - a tradition we wanted to conceptualize in a beer.

Utilizing freshly stone-milled Massachusetts flour, we baked loaves in our wood-fired ovens in Canton and added the resulting bread to the mash of a beer we're ready to share with you in the coming days. More info coming soon!

node.text:
Our first collaboration with @burialbeer is a celebration of shared values. Incorporating local ingredients into our beers and on our restaurants' plates, thereby supporting a healthier, regional agricultural system is a cornerstone of both company's missions.

This Double IPA hones in on that concept, incorporating Tuxpeño Corn grown by David Bauer of @farmandsparrow in Mars Hill, NC and sourced from @epiphanycraftmalt in Durham, as well as @valleymalt wheat from our @northeastgrains partners in Hadley, MA.

Hopped with Mosaic, Rakau, and Strata, Panicle Initiation offers waves of lychee gummies, sticky pineapple purèe, and scoops of mango gelato. The fluffy mouthfeel is complemented by a nuanced, underlying grain profile, thanks in part to the cereal mash we employed for the Tuxpeño.

Cans will be available to purchase tomorrow at 9 AM for both UPS Direct, as well as Pick Up in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point. 8.0% ABV. $22.20/4-pack, limit one case per person. Stay tuned for information regarding collaboration merch, to be posted tomorrow morning!
